FBIS4-60374 "drnes100_l_94013" FBIS-NES-94-100 Daily Report 24 May 1994 ISRAEL Defense Sources Reject Red Cross Visit to al-Dirani Defense Sources Reject Red Cross Visit to al-Dirani TA2405101894 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 24 May 94 pp A1, A10 TA2405101894 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ Hebrew BFN [Report by military affairs correspondent Eytan Rabin] [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Defense establishment elements announced yesterday that Israel will not permit International Committee of the Red Cross [ICRC] representatives to visit al-Dirani as long as no sign of life is received from Ron Arad. The announcement was made in response to an ICRC appeal to the Israeli Government to allow its staffers to visit al-Dirani. [passage omitted]
